# PostgreSQL Setup Guide

Your project has been generated with PostgreSQL and Prisma support. Follow these steps to get your database up and running.

## 1. Install PostgreSQL

If you don't have PostgreSQL installed, you can download it from [postgresql.org](https://www.postgresql.org/download/).

Alternatively, if you enabled the **Docker** feature, you can run PostgreSQL using Docker Compose:

```bash
docker-compose up -d postgres
```

## 2. Configure DATABASE_URL

Open your `.env` file and ensure the `DATABASE_URL` is correct.

Example:
```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/app_db
```

## 3. Run Prisma Migrations

To create the database tables based on your `prisma/schema.prisma`, run:

```bash
<%= PACKAGE_MANAGER %> run prisma:migrate
```

This will also generate the Prisma Client.

## 4. Run Prisma Generate

If you make changes to `prisma/schema.prisma`, run:

```bash
<%= PACKAGE_MANAGER %> run prisma:generate
```

## 5. Prisma Studio

To view and edit your data in a GUI, run:

```bash
<%= PACKAGE_MANAGER %> run prisma:studio
```

## 6. Start the Application

```bash
<%= PACKAGE_MANAGER %> run dev
```
